author: fitz
msg: *checkout-cmd.c: Added enormous comment re: checking out multiple
repositories, now feeding multiples to the svn_client_checkout
command, and have (gladly) ditched all that ancestor-path
foolishness.
*cl.h: removed svn_cl__target_dir_opt from svn_cl__longopt_t since it
now has 'd' as its shortopt
*main.c: - checkout command now takes 1 or more non-file targets.
- fixed checkout helpstring
- deep-sixed ancestor-path related code as it's now a
non-file arg to checkout
- renamed --target-dir to --destination and made -d the
short-opt (see README)
- non-file arg descriptions that have -1 in them (like the
one for svn checkout) require at least one arg. Seems right
to me... I don't see the case where we would ever have 0,
1, or many non-file args. This can always change in the future.
*tests/svn-test.sh: updated to accomodate new calling conventions.
*tests/svn-test2.sh: updated to accomodate new calling conventions.
